This directory contains lists of absorption and emission lines as well as
common and header files for RVSAO and information needed to access RVSAO
help files.

Help files:

Use these with softools.mkhelpdb if package is named rvsao
  root.hd
  rootrvsao.hd
to make
  helpdb.mip

Use these with softools.mkhelpdb if package is named r2rvsao
  root2.hd
  rootrvsao2.hd
to make
  helpdb.mip (or rename helpdb2.mip)

Line Lists:

Defaults:
  ablines.dat	Galaxy absorption lines
  emlines.dat	Galaxy emission lines
  emsrch.dat	Galaxy lines for emsao.vel_init="search"
  emcomb.dat	Galaxy combination lines
  badlines.dat	Night sky lines which may cause problems

Other files of lines to remove:
  badskyo.dat	Night sky OI lines which may cause problems
  badskynao.dat	Night sky Na and OI lines which may cause problems

Other files of lines to search:
  emhsrch.dat	

Files for night sky emission line fits using EMSAO
  mkosky.dat	Night sky lines at Mauna Kea, including brightest OH lines
  mkoskyall.dat Night sky lines at Mauna Kea, including all OH lines to 7000 A
  skylines.dat	Reliable night sky lines
  skysearch.dat	Sky lines for emsao.vel_init="search"
  skycomb.dat	Sky combination lines
  skynao.dat	skylines.dat without 4046 Hg line
  skyolines.dat	Night sky OI lines only

Line lists for LINESPEC
  skytemp.dat	Input file to make a fake night sky spectrum
  emtemp.dat	Input file to make a fake galaxy emission spectrum

Alternate lines to display:
  emlineshe.dat  Helium star emission lines
  emlineshe2.dat Exploding star HeI and HeII emission lines
                 from L.H.Aller, "Gaseous Nebulae" NY: John Wiley, 1956, p.60ff
